block content
  h1 We Love Tinynodes

  p
    | Traditional web application development on any scale can lead to an array of
    | problems. Large code bases that become harder to debug, maintain and
    | improve over time.
  p
    | At Tinynodes it's all about building applications using
    | smaller, discrete bits of functionality.  Every part of your application is designed as
    | it's own service that isn't tied to any specific part of the system.
  p
    | Web front-ends don't need to be tied to the database - they can instead call
    | RESTful or websocket based services that can live anywhere in the network and
    | make requests to obtain data - your own, or from third-party services.

  h2 A Different Development Methodology

  p
    | Tinynodes is the application development and consultancy services of&nbsp;
    a(href='http://zerp.ly/tanepiper', title='My Zerply Profile') Tane Piper

  p
    | I take a different approach to developing web applications - instead of the
    | 'kitchen sink' approach of putting everything into one code base,
    | your application is developed with individual components in mind. Each can
    | 'speak' to each other - be it on local machines, or over the internet.

  p
    | These components are re-usable and can run as one-or-many instances. For example
    | you may have an application that reads and writes to twitter - my approach would
    | be to have an application for each, sharing a common code base and OAuth library -
    | this means it's much easier to maintain
    | and update each one, without affecting other parts of the application.

  p
    | I provide consultancy services and&nbsp;
    a(href='http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/DevOps', target='_new') devops
    |&nbsp;services, building applications
    | using the latest technology and platforms built for the web.

  p
    | Many of the technology available today can be confusing, and to make sure
    | you choose the right one for your app we'll investigate what would be the
    | best fit

