  h2 Working together with trust and respect

  p
    | I am open and up-front about working with my clients, and their needs - constant
    | and clear communication is key to any successful project - especially with remote
    | working.

  p
    | I do not take on fixed-price projects unless they meet a minimum requirement - I, and
    | many developers like me have been burned in the past with this - and it's one of the
    | major areas that can cause tension and burn-out between client and developer.

  p
    | Projects are not taken on without a minimum specification - a client can certainly welcome to approach me
    | with a vauge idea in their head about what they need - but without working together to
    | clearly define project goals, many projects will have a lot of friction and tend to fail.

  p
    | I do not sign NDAs - an NDA is a sign of a lack of, or broken trust between parties.

